The paper discusses the formation and performance of teams, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and social computing (cs.SI). The paper also mentions the importance of organisational psychology, which falls under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY) and computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper discusses the potential for cross-fertilisation between computer science and psychology, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
